<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <!-- Required meta tags -->
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, shrink-to-fit=no">

    <!-- Bootstrap CSS -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="bootstrap-5.0.2/dist/css/bootstrap-grid.min.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="bootstrap-5.0.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    <!-- Font Awesome CSS -->
    <link href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/5.4.1/css/all.min.css" rel="stylesheet"
        type='text/css'>
    <!--CSS-->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/mainPage.css">

    <title>Tutorial</title>
</head>
<style>
    .margin-center {
        padding: 5%;
    }

    p {
        font-size: large;
    }

    .round {
        border-radius: 25px;
    }
</style>

<body>
    <nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg bg-body-tertiary navbar bg-dark" data-bs-theme="dark">
        <div class="container-fluid">
            <a class="navbar-brand" href="#">Task-O-Pad</a>
            <button style="color: #ffffff" class="navbar-toggler" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                data-bs-target="#navbarNavDropdown" aria-controls="navbarNavDropdown" aria-expanded="false"
                aria-label="Toggle navigation">
                <span class="navbar-toggler-icon">â†¨</span>
            </button>
            <div class="collapse navbar-collapse navbar-default" id="navbarNavDropdown">
                <ul class="navbar-nav">
                    <li class="nav-item">
                        <form action="/" method="GET">
                            <input class="nav-link nav-button" type="submit" value="Home" />
                        </form>
                    </li>
                    <% if(connected) { %>
                        <li class="nav-item">
                            <form action="/tasks" method="GET">
                                <input class="nav-link nav-button" type="submit" value="Tasks" />
                            </form>
                        </li>
                        <% } %>
                            <li class="nav-item">
                                <% if(connected) { %>
                                    <form action="/logout" method="GET">
                                        <input class="nav-link nav-button" type="submit" value="Logout" />
                                    </form>
                                    <% } else { %>
                                        <form action="/login" method="GET">
                                            <input class="nav-link nav-button" type="submit" value="Login" />
                                        </form>
                            <li class="nav-item">
                                <form action="/signup" method="GET">
                                    <input class="nav-link nav-button" type="submit" value="Sign Up" />
                                </form>
                            </li>
                            <% } %>
                                </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </nav>


    <div class="sectionLight">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-sm-12">
                <div class="mt-4 p-5 text-black rounded jumbotron">
                    <h1>Tutorial</h1>
                    <p>Below this is a provided tutorial page on how to use the "Tasks" aspect of the website</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- SECTION TWO -->

        <div class="sectionDark round">
            <!-- FIRST ROW -->
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
                    <img class="img-fluid" src="assets/Tutorial1.png" width="949" height="542">
                </div>
                <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-sm-12">
                            <p>The image on the left shows the first thing you will be presented with once you navigate
                                your way to the
                                "Tasks" page, in this part we will talk about the basics of our website and how to use
                                it
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-12">
                            <div class="margin-center">
                                <p>1. In order to add a new project or add a new task to an existing project you will
                                    need to press on the "Add Task"
                                    button on the left side.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    2 + 3. In order to delete an existing project you will need to select said project
                                    from the drop down list labelled
                                    "Select Project" and then you will need to press the "Delete Project" button on the
                                    right side.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    4 + 5. In order to search for a specific task or a specific project, press on
                                    "Select a date" date-picker
                                    and choose a date to show all tasks with that specific start date, alternatively you
                                    can press on "Search Task"
                                    text field and type a name of a task in order to show all tasks with that name.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    6. All tasks will be shown in the table shown
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    7. In order to save changes made, press the "Save Changes" button, all changes will
                                    immediately be pushed to the
                                    database, note that this action is irreversible
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <br>

            <!-- SECOND ROW -->
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
                    <img class="img-fluid" src="assets/Tutorial2.png" width="949" height="542">
                </div>
                <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-sm-12">
                            <p>The image on the left shows what happens if you press on the "Add Task" button
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-12">
                            <div class="margin-center">
                                <p>1. In order to select a project that already exists, press the "Select Project"
                                    dropdown list and choose a project.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    2 + 3. In order to create a new project, press the "Project Name" text field and
                                    enter a project name, afterwards
                                    press the "Add Project" button.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    4 + 5 + 6. In order to add a new task, first choose (or create) a project using the
                                    methods 1. and 2 + 3.
                                    after wards press the "What are you planning to do?" text field and enter the task
                                    discription and finally press the
                                    "Supposed Start Date" date-picker and choose a starting date.
                                    And finally press the "Add Task" button.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <br>

            <!-- THIRD ROW -->
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
                    <img class="img-fluid" src="assets/Tutorial3.png" width="949" height="542">
                </div>
                <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-sm-12">
                            <p>The image on the left shows what happens if you press on the "Add Task" button
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-12">
                            <div class="margin-center">
                                <p>1. In order to edit a task, press on it's name and you will be presented with a new window
                                    with all the task's information
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    2 + 3 + 4 Here you can see the task's information which include the Project's name, it's status
                                    and the date in which it was added.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    5. In order to change a task's status press the "Change Status" button and choose the new status
                                    you wish the task to have (which includes the option to delete a certain task).
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <br>

            <!-- FOURTH ROW -->
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
                    <img class="img-fluid" src="assets/Tutorial4.png" width="949" height="542">
                </div>
                <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-sm-12">
                            <p>The image on the left shows what happens if you press on the task name highlighted in
                                blue (edit task page)
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-12">
                            <div class="margin-center">
                                <p>1. In order to change the name of a task, press on the text field which has the task
                                    name in it, and write the
                                    desired task name.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    2. In order to change the supposed start date of the task, press on the date-picker
                                    and choose the desired
                                    supposed start date.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    3. In order to save the changes made, press on the "Edit Task" button.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>


        <!-- FOOTER -->
    </div>
    <footer class="footer bg-light-gray">
        <div class="container-fluid">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-sm-4 col-lg-3">
                    <img class="img-fluid footer-img" src="assets/TaskOPad.png">
                </div>
                <div id="icons" class="col-sm-8 col-lg-8 margin center">
                    <!-- Facebook -->
                    <a class="btn btn-floating m-1" href="https://www.facebook.com/" role="button"><i
                            class="fab fa-facebook fa-lg"></i></i></a>
                    <!-- Twitter -->
                    <a class="btn btn-floating m-1" href="https://twitter.com/?lang=en" role="button"><i
                            class="fab fa-twitter fa-lg"></i></i></a>
                    <!-- Google -->
                    <a class="btn btn-floating m-1" href="https://www.google.com/" role="button"><i
                            class="fab fa-google fa-lg"></i></i></a>
                    <!-- Instagram -->
                    <a class="btn btn-floating m-1" href="https://www.instagram.com/" role="button"><i
                            class="fab fa-instagram fa-lg"></i></i></a>
                    <!-- Linkedin -->
                    <a class="btn btn-floating m-1" href="https://il.linkedin.com/" role="button"><i
                            class="fab fa-linkedin fa-lg"></i></i></a>
                    <!-- Github -->
                    <a class="btn btn-floating m-1" href="https://github.com/" role="button"><i
                            class="fab fa-github fa-lg"></i></i></a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </footer>



